claim.claim-text:
1. Bone anchoring device including

an anchoring element (1) having a shaft (2) for anchoring in the bone and a head (3),

a receiving part (5"') having a top end (5a) and a bottom end (5b), a channel (11) for receiving the rod (6) near the top end and an accommodation space (9a, 9b) for accommodating the head near the bottom end, the accommodation space having an opening (10) towards the bottom end, the opening being sized so as to allow the introduction of the head (3) from the bottom end;

a pressure element (8"'), the pressure element being located at least partly in the accommodation space and having a flexible portion (85) to clamp the head;

wherein the anchoring element is pivotable with respect to the receiving part and can be fixed at an angle by moving the pressure element inside the accommodation space such that the head (3) is locked within the flexible portion (85) of the pressure element;

wherein the pressure element (8"') comprises a first threaded section (830) which is coupled to a second threaded section (930) at the inner wall of the receiving part (5"') when the pressure element is inserted into the receiving part to prevent loss of the pressure element from the receiving part,

wherein a secured state is obtained by screwing the pressure element through the threaded section (930) until it is accommodated in the accommodation space (9a, 9b),

wherein the height of the threaded section (830) of the pressure element (8"') in an axial direction is small compared to height of a substantially cylindrical section of the pressure element (8"').
